1972年6月22日，{{tsl|en|Hurricane Agnes|颶風艾格尼絲}}在紐約州東南部登陸，並向西移至賓夕法尼亞州<ref name="NWS@200114"/><ref name="SRBC_Hurricane Agnes">{{Cite web |url = https://www.srbc.net/our-work/fact-sheets/docs/tropical-storm-agnes-june-1972.pdf |title = TROPICAL STORM AGNES IN THESUSQUEHANNA RIVER BASIN |author = Susquehanna River Basin Commission |year = 2018 |language = en |accessdate = 2021-05-15 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210318032822/https://www.srbc.net/our-work/fact-sheets/docs/tropical-storm-agnes-june-1972.pdf |archivedate = 2021-03-18}}</ref>。而在21日至24日之間，艾格尼絲帶來大範圍暴雨，其中賓夕法尼亞州和紐約州西部更錄得250至460毫米（10至18英寸）的降雨量，而大部分降水則從西部支流流入主河段<ref name="SRBC_Hurricane Agnes"/>。隨後流域多地發生洪災，範圍遠至紐約州賓漢頓以及馬利蘭州迪博伊西港<ref name="SRBC_Hurricane Agnes"/>。河流最高水位在哈里斯堡一帶上升至10.14米（33.27英尺），超越1936年3月洪水創下的紀錄，是自1786年有紀錄以來最高<ref name="NWS@200114"/><ref name="SRBC_Hurricane Agnes"/>。懷俄明谷是賓州受災最為嚴重的地區，洪水幾乎淹浸整個山谷，超過2萬間房屋、2,700家企業和150家工廠遭到破壞，區內許多[[維多利亞時代|維多利亞時代]]的歷史建築亦受損嚴重至無法修復<ref name="TL@170618">{{Cite web |url = https://www.timesleader.com/news/local/663873/45-years-later-agnes-still-on-peoples-minds |title = 45 years later, Agnes still on people’s minds |date = 2017-06-18 |publisher = Times Leader |language = en |accessdate = 2021-05-15 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210515143859/https://www.timesleader.com/news/local/663873/45-years-later-agnes-still-on-peoples-minds |archivedate = 2021-05-15}}</ref>。最終，洪災在流域內奪去72人的性命，並造成約28億美元損失<ref name="SRBC_Hurricane Agnes"/>。同時，河流向車薩比灣排放大量淡水，對海灣北部的水生植物和魚類群落帶來短暫影響{{sfn|Ruzecki, et al.|1976|pp=399, 460-462}}。1979年3月28日，由於工作人員錯誤操作加上機械故障，導致位於哈里斯堡東南部的[[三哩島核電廠|三哩島核電廠]][[三哩島事件|發生爐心熔毀事故]]<ref name="Peterson@WSP_890328">{{cite news |url = https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/national/longterm/tmi/stories/decade032889.htm |title = A Decade Later, TMI's Legacy Is Mistrust |last = Peterson |first = Cass |date = 1989-03-28 |publisher = The Washington Post |page = A01 |language = en |accessdate = 2021-05-16 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210516082924/https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/national/longterm/tmi/stories/decade032889.htm |archivedate = 2021-05-16}}</ref>。儘管爐心熔解可控而且輻射洩漏量很低，但時任州長{{tsl|en|Dick Thornburgh|迪克·索恩伯格}}仍聽取[[美國核能管理委員會|美國核能管理委員會]]主席{{tsl|en|Joseph Hendrie|約瑟夫·亨德里}}的建議，疏散核電廠8公里（5英里）半徑範圍內的孕婦和學齡前兒童，並要求16公里（10英里）半徑範圍內的居民留於家中並關上門窗<ref name="Peterson@WSP_890328"/>{{sfn|Cutter|Barnes|1982|pp=116-117}}。在短短數日之內，數以十萬計的居民撤離受影響區域<ref name="Peterson@WSP_890328"/>{{sfn|Cutter|Barnes|1982|p=118}}。縱使核能管理委員會後來指事件未有為公共安全和周圍居民的健康帶來負面影響<ref name="NRC_Three Mile Island Accident">{{Cite web |url = https://www.nrc.gov/reading-rm/doc-collections/fact-sheets/3mile-isle.html |title = Backgrounder on the Three Mile Island Accident |author = United States Nuclear Regulatory Commission |date = 2018-06-21 |language = en |accessdate = 2021-05-16 |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20211115101945/https://www.nrc.gov/reading-rm/doc-collections/fact-sheets/3mile-isle.html |archivedate = 2021-11-15 }}</ref>，但仍成為接下來連月多場全國性反核示威活動的導火線，其中在哈里斯堡至少有6.5萬名示威者參與遊行<ref name="WSP@790507">{{Cite web |url = https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/politics/1979/05/07/the-protesters/b2ea631e-933c-4f07-b59e-e97bf1068b7e/ |title = The Protesters |last1 = Valentine |first1 = Paul W. |last2 = Barker |first2 = Karlyn |author3 = Washington Post Staff Writers |date = 1979-05-07 |publisher = The Washington Post |language = en |accessdate = 2021-01-02 |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20211109080947/https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/politics/1979/05/07/the-protesters/b2ea631e-933c-4f07-b59e-e97bf1068b7e/ |archivedate = 2021-11-09 }}</ref>。1997年，美國國家環境保護局把河流上游及支流拉克萬納河列為{{tsl|en|American Heritage Rivers|美國遺產河流}}<ref>{{Cite web |url = http://www.epa.gov/rivers/98rivers/susquehanna.html |title = Upper Susquehanna and Lackawanna Rivers (PA) |author = U.S. Environmental Protection Agency |language = en |accessdate = 2021-05-17 |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20061003011033/http://www.epa.gov/rivers/98rivers/susquehanna.html|archivedate = 2006-10-03}}</ref>。

位於[[鏽帶|鏽帶]]的城市（如賓漢頓和威爾克斯-巴里）自20世紀中葉開始經歷了數十年的[[去工業化|去工業化]]、人口流失和城市衰退{{sfn|Eisenstadt|2005|p=851}}<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/aliahanna/i-grew-up-in-the-rust-belt-but-im-not-in-any-of-the-stories |title = To Understand The Rust Belt, We Need To See Beyond Whiteness |last = Habib |first = Alia Hanna |date = 2017-01-12 |publisher = Buzz Feed News |language = en |accessdate = 2021-05-19 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210308174647/https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/aliahanna/i-grew-up-in-the-rust-belt-but-im-not-in-any-of-the-stories |archivedate = 2021-03-08}}</ref>。21世紀初，這些城市均進行產業轉型以刺激和振興當地經濟，而賓漢頓把其主要產業由製造業轉為醫療保健業便是其中一個例子<ref>{{Cite web |url = http://www.pressconnects.com/article/20130619/BUSINESS/306200007/0/news01/Southern-Tier-jobs-shift-from-manufacturing-to-service-industry |title = Southern Tier jobs shift from manufacturing to service industry |last = Harris |first = Jon |date = 2013-06-19 |publisher = Press & Sun-Bulletin |language = en |accessdate = 2021-05-19 |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://archive.ph/20130831192917/http://www.pressconnects.com/article/20130619/BUSINESS/306200007/0/news01/Southern-Tier-jobs-shift-from-manufacturing-to-service-industry |archivedate = 2013-08-31}}</ref>。2011年9月初，[[2011年熱帶風暴李|熱帶風暴李]]吹襲[[美國墨西哥灣沿岸地區|美國墨西哥灣沿岸地區]]和[[美國東部|美國東部]]<ref name="Brown@111215">{{Cite web |url = https://www.nhc.noaa.gov/data/tcr/AL132011_Lee.pdf |title = Tropical Cyclone Report: Tropical Storm Lee (AL132011) 2-5 September 2011 |last = Brown |first = Daniel P. |date = 2011-12-15 |publisher = National Hurricane Center |language = en |accessdate = 2021-05-22 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210521200124/https://www.nhc.noaa.gov/data/tcr/AL132011_Lee.pdf |archivedate = 2021-05-21}}</ref>。風暴殘餘物為流域帶來大雨，並在多地引發洪災<ref name="Brown@111215"/>。其中，賓漢頓一帶所錄得的降雨量為250至300毫米（10至12英寸），美國地質調查局在鄰近河段設置的監測站更錄得河流水位較其洪水位高出5.2米（17英尺）<ref name="Brown@111215"/><ref>{{Cite web |url = https://water.weather.gov/ahps2/hydrograph.php?wfo=bgm&gage=vstn6 |title = Advanced Hydrologic Prediction Service: Binghamton: Susquehanna River at Vestal |author = National Weather Service |language = en |accessdate = 2021-05-22 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210326151126/https://water.weather.gov/ahps2/hydrograph.php?wfo=bgm&gage=vstn6 |archivedate = 2021-03-26}}</ref>。洪水來襲導致賓漢頓以西的[[奧韋戈村_(紐約州)|奧韋戈村]]幾乎被淹沒，而布魯姆縣亦有2萬多居民需要撤離<ref>{{Cite web |url = http://www.nytimes.com/2011/09/09/nyregion/remnants-of-tropical-storm-soak-an-already-battered-northeast.html |title = Northeast Is Soaked Again, Forcing Evacuations |last = Flegenheimer |first = Matt |date = 2011-09-08 |publisher = The New York Times |language = en |accessdate = 2021-05-22 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210410220657/http://www.nytimes.com/2011/09/09/nyregion/remnants-of-tropical-storm-soak-an-already-battered-northeast.html |archivedate = 2021-04-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.weather.gov/media/marfc/MARFC_FcstPt/NBS/Owego.pdf |title = (North Branch) Susquehanna River at Owego, New York |author = National Weather Service |language = en |accessdate = 2021-05-22 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20170802190816/http://www.weather.gov/media/marfc/MARFC_FcstPt/NBS/Owego.pdf |archivedate = 2017-08-02}}</ref>。而在賓夕法尼亞州，盧澤恩縣受災最為嚴重，威爾克斯-巴里、愛德華茲維爾、西皮茨頓等城鎮被淹，縣政府更下令所有曾受1972年颶風艾格尼絲洪災影響的地區須強制撤離，而鄰近河段的水位亦一度升至13米（42.66英尺），打破1972年洪災的紀錄<ref name="Brown@111215"/><ref name="TL@150619">{{Cite web |url = https://www.timesleader.com/archive/249989/stories-county-could-see-2416-million-flood-aid8476-2 |title = County could see $16 million flood aid |date = 2015-06-19 |publisher = Times Leader |language = en |accessdate = 2021-05-22 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210522141319/https://www.timesleader.com/archive/249989/stories-county-could-see-2416-million-flood-aid8476-2 |archivedate = 2021-05-22}}</ref>。在哈里斯堡，市政府撤離逾萬名居於市中心低窪地區的居民，而在稍後時間河流水位上升2.1米（7英尺），淹沒城市島（{{lang|en|City Island}}）及市內低窪地區<ref name="Brown@111215"/><ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.pennlive.com/midstate/2011/09/post_237.html |title = Harrisburg announces flood evacuation of up to 10,000 residents from Front to Third streets |date = 2011-09-08 |publisher = PennLive.com |language = en |accessdate = 2021-05-22 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210410225451/https://www.pennlive.com/midstate/2011/09/post_237.html |archivedate = 2021-04-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.weather.gov/ctp/TSLeeFlooding |title = 4th Anniversary of the Flooding from Tropical Storm Lee |author = National Weather Service |language = en |accessdate = 2021-05-22 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210512124524/https://www.weather.gov/ctp/TSLeeFlooding |archivedate = 2021-05-12}}</ref>。是次洪災造成多人死亡，紐約州布魯姆縣和泰奧加縣分別損失5.13億美元和4.78億美元，而賓夕法尼亞州道芬縣和盧澤恩縣則分別蒙受1.5億美元及數千萬美元損失<ref name="TL@150619"/><ref>{{Cite web |url = http://www.pressconnects.com/article/20120201/NEWS01/202010330/Tier-flood-damage-estimate-1-billion |title = Tier flood damage estimate: $1 billion |last = Micale |first = Jennifer |date = 2012-02-01 |publisher = PressConnect |language = en |accessdate = 2021-05-22 |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://archive.ph/dSW9 |archivedate = 2012-09-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.pennlive.com/midstate/2011/09/agencies_starting_to_compile_l.html |title = Agencies starting to compile lists of damages from Tropical Storm Lee |last = Dobeneck |first = Monica Von |date = 2011-09-15 |publisher = PennLive.com |language = en |accessdate = 2021-05-22 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210522142839/https://www.pennlive.com/midstate/2011/09/agencies_starting_to_compile_l.html |archivedate = 2021-05-22}}</ref>。2019年9月20日，[[艾索倫電力公司|艾索倫電力公司]]宣佈三哩島核電廠正式停止運作，而廠內的所有放射性物質則預計需要60年才能完全清理<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.exeloncorp.com/newsroom/three-mile-island-generating-station-unit-1-retires |title = Three Mile Island Generating Station Unit 1 Retires from Service After 45 Years |author = Exelon Corporation |date = 2019-09-19 |language = en |accessdate = 2021-05-29 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210318174315/https://www.exeloncorp.com/newsroom/three-mile-island-generating-station-unit-1-retires |archivedate = 2021-03-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url = https://lancasteronline.com/news/pennsylvania/after-announcement-of-closure-what-s-next-for-three-mile/article_03d990ac-4535-11e7-a633-9394126c60ff.html |title = After announcement of closure, what's next for Three Mile Island nuclear plant? |last = Crable |first = AD |date = 2017-05-30 |publisher = LancasterOnline |language = en |accessdate = 2021-05-29 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20190119005431/https://lancasteronline.com/news/pennsylvania/after-announcement-of-closure-what-s-next-for-three-mile/article_03d990ac-4535-11e7-a633-9394126c60ff.html |archivedate = 2019-01-19}}</ref>。2020年9月10日，馬里蘭州、哥倫比亞特區、維吉尼亞邦和德拉瓦州，以及車薩比灣基金會和其合作伙伴，分別向[[美國哥倫比亞特區聯邦地區法院|美國哥倫比亞特區聯邦地區法院]]提交訴狀，控告美國國家環境保護局未有履行一項旨在減少車薩比灣污染的十年協議，同時未有要求賓夕法尼亞州和紐約州制定計劃以減少污染物藉薩斯奎哈納河流入海灣<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/legal-issues/three-states-and-dc-sue-epa-saying-the-agency-failed-to-enforce-plan-to-reduce-chesapeake-bay-pollution/2020/09/10/8a55dbc6-f37f-11ea-999c-67ff7bf6a9d2_story.html |title = Three states and D.C. sue EPA, saying the agency failed to enforce plan to reduce Chesapeake Bay pollution |last = Davies |first = Emily |date = 2020-09-11 |publisher = The Washington Post |language = en |accessdate = 2021-07-07 |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20211109081134/https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/legal-issues/three-states-and-dc-sue-epa-saying-the-agency-failed-to-enforce-plan-to-reduce-chesapeake-bay-pollution/2020/09/10/8a55dbc6-f37f-11ea-999c-67ff7bf6a9d2_story.html |archivedate = 2021-11-09 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.cbf.org/news-media/newsroom/2020/federal/cbf-to-sue-epa-over-failure-to-hold-pennsylvania-and-new-york-accountable.html |title = CBF to Sue EPA over Failure to Hold Pennsylvania and New York Accountable for Not Meeting Clean Water Act Obligations |author = Chesapeake Bay Foundation |date = 2020-09-10 |language = en |accessdate = 2021-07-07 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210514145440/https://www.cbf.org/news-media/newsroom/2020/federal/cbf-to-sue-epa-over-failure-to-hold-pennsylvania-and-new-york-accountable.html |archivedate = 2021-05-14}}</ref>。

== 河流改造 ==
[[File:Pennsylvania_canals.png|thumb]]
[[File:Conowingo_Dam_2016.jpg|thumb]]
在19世紀以前，1.6公里（1英里）寬的薩斯奎哈納河是人們往返南北各州的一道屏障，他們只能依賴渡輪過河<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.cecildaily.com/our_cecil/cecil-history-a-bridge-over-the-river-susquehanna/article_c82fb7a8-57da-11e2-b6ba-0019bb2963f4.html |title = Cecil history: A bridge over the river Susquehanna |last = Sturgill |first = Erika Quesenbery |date = 2013-01-06 |publisher = Cecil Whig |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-05 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210605104825/https://www.cecildaily.com/our_cecil/cecil-history-a-bridge-over-the-river-susquehanna/article_c82fb7a8-57da-11e2-b6ba-0019bb2963f4.html |archivedate = 2021-05-06}}</ref>。河流還存在不少急流，船隻只能利用春季融雪水造成的河水暴漲順流而下，而無法逆流而上{{sfn|Livingood|1941|pp=131-132}}{{sfn|Myers|1948|pp=159-160}}。1818年，{{tsl|en|Port Deposit Bridge|迪博伊西港橋}}建成<ref name="Sturgill@CW_190420">{{Cite web |url = https://www.cecildaily.com/our_cecil/a-burr-in-the-susquehanna-river/article_44a86d8d-2dfe-5943-a8f9-30c394030a55.html |title = A ‘Burr’ in the Susquehanna River |last = Sturgill |first = Erika Quesenbery |date = 2019-04-20 |publisher = Cecil Whig |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-08 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210608133630/https://www.cecildaily.com/our_cecil/a-burr-in-the-susquehanna-river/article_44a86d8d-2dfe-5943-a8f9-30c394030a55.html |archivedate = 2021-06-08}}</ref>。這座木製廊橋長1,270米（4,170英尺），設有18個跨距61米（200英尺）的拱形桁架，是當時首條橫跨河流並連接南北兩岸的橋樑<ref name="Sturgill@CW_190420"/>。廊橋後來被洪水摧毀，最終在1859年被位於更上游的科諾溫哥橋取代<ref name="Sturgill@CW_190420"/>。1902年，位於哈里斯堡上方的{{tsl|en|Rockville Bridge|羅克維爾橋}}建成，它長1,160米（3,820英尺），在當時屬世界上最長的石砌拱形鐵路高架橋{{sfn|Treese|2003|p=77}}。橋樑在1975年被聯邦政府列入《[[國家史蹟名錄|國家史蹟名錄]]》，並在1979年被美國土木工程師學會評選為[[國際土木工程歷史古蹟|國際土木工程歷史古蹟]]{{sfn|Treese|2003|p=77}}。另外，河流的通航能力在1820年代亦開始得到改善<ref name="PHMC_Pennsylvania Canals"/>。1828年，聯盟運河建成，並成功把哈里斯堡河段與斯庫爾基爾河連接起來{{sfn|Shank|1986|pp=7-9}}。聯盟運河長132公里（82英里），寬36米（11英尺），深1.2米（4英尺），並設有93個船閘{{sfn|Shank|1986|pp=7-9}}。可是，由於建造船閘時出現明顯錯誤，導致運河的船閘太窄和太小<ref name="Duff@TBS_050626">{{Cite web |url = https://www.baltimoresun.com/news/bs-xpm-2005-06-26-0506160308-story.html |title = Susquehanna canal in Confederate path |last = Duff |first = Robert M. |date = 2005-06-26 |publisher = The Baltimore Sun |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-05 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210622193136/https://www.baltimoresun.com/news/bs-xpm-2005-06-26-0506160308-story.html |archivedate = 2021-06-22 }}</ref>。到了1830年代，賓夕凡尼亞州政府和運河公司先後在河流下游興建兩條運河系統來繞過急流。1831年，由賓州政府出資興建的{{tsl|en|Pennsylvania Canal (Susquehanna Division)|薩斯奎哈納運河}}正式啟用{{sfn|Shank|1986|pp=49-51}}。運河長66公里（41英里），始於諾森伯蘭，終於朱尼亞塔河河口的{{tsl|en|Duncan Island (36LA60,61)|鄧肯島 (賓夕法尼亞州蘭開斯特縣)|鄧肯島}}，沿途設有12個船閘，能克服河中約26米（86英尺）的高度落差{{sfn|Shank|1986|pp=49-51}}。而在1840年，位於賓州賴茨維爾與馬利蘭州哈弗格雷斯之間的{{tsl|en|Susquehanna and Tidewater Canal|薩斯奎哈納和潮水運河}}亦落成{{sfn|Shank|1986|pp=69-72}}。運河長69公里（43英里），寬15米（50英尺），深約1.8米（6英尺），設有29個船閘，能克服70米（231英尺）的高度落差{{sfn|Shank|1986|pp=69-72}}。隨著工業時代的發展，這類內陸運河逐漸被鐵路取代，幾乎所有運河都在1901年被停用和廢棄<ref name="PHMC_Pennsylvania Canals"/>。時至今日，大多運河遺址已被水淹浸，或被保育成為歷史公園的一部分{{sfn|Shank|1986|p=5}}。

薩斯奎哈納河上築有十多個水壩<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.chesapeakeconservancy.org/images/Susquehanna_Map_small.pdf |title = Envision the Susquehanna |author = National Geographic |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-19 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210921212027/https://www.chesapeakeconservancy.org/images/Susquehanna_Map_small.pdf |archivedate = 2021-09-21 }}</ref>，而其中較重要的三個水壩則集中在下游<ref name="EPA@101229">{{Cite web |url = https://www.epa.gov/sites/production/files/2015-02/documents/appendix_t_susquehanna_dams_final.pdf |title = Appendix T. - Chesapeake Bay TMDL |author = U.S. Environmental Protection Agency |date = 2010-12-29 |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-12 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210327074452/https://www.epa.gov/sites/production/files/2015-02/documents/appendix_t_susquehanna_dams_final.pdf |archivedate = 2021-03-27}}</ref>。在1931年建成的{{tsl|en|Safe Harbor Dam|安全港水壩}}屬[[重力壩|混凝土重力壩]]，長1,484米（4,869英尺），高23米（75英尺），並設有3個雙摺葉調節閘門和28個防洪閘{{sfn|Federal Energy Regulatory Commission|1982|p=63,909}}<ref name="MD-DNR@2016_Appendix K">{{Cite web |url = https://dnr.maryland.gov/waters/bay/Documents/LSRWA/Reports/AppK.pdf |title = Appendix K: Existing Conditions of the Watershed |author = Maryland Department of Natural Resources |year = 2016 |publisher = State of Maryland |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-13 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201106061058/https://dnr.maryland.gov/waters/bay/Documents/LSRWA/Reports/AppK.pdf |archivedate = 2020-11-06}}</ref>。其水庫{{tsl|en|Lake Clarke|克拉克湖}}面積為27.2平方公里（6,720英畝），最大蓄水量為59,020,000立方米（47,850英畝·英尺）{{sfn|Federal Energy Regulatory Commission|1982|p=63,909}}。{{tsl|en|Holtwood Dam|霍爾特伍德水壩}}於1910年啟用，是採用溢流型結構的混凝土重力壩，長729米（2,392英尺），高17米（55英尺），其水庫阿爾德雷德湖（{{lang|en|Lake Aldred}}）面積為9.7平方公里（2,400英畝）<ref>{{Cite web |url = http://www.chesapeake.org/conowingo_model/downloads/rep/WEST,%202017a.%20Lake%20Clarke%20and%20Lake%20Aldred%20Sediment%20Transport%20Modeling%20-%20Final.pdf |title = Lake Clarke and Lake AldredSediment Transport Modeling |author = WEST Consultants |year = 2017 |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-12 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210327074452/https://www.epa.gov/sites/production/files/2015-02/documents/appendix_t_susquehanna_dams_final.pdf |archivedate = 2021-03-27}}</ref><ref name="LIHI-Holtwood Dam">{{Cite web |url = https://lowimpacthydro.org/lihi-certificate-116-holtwood-hydroelectric-project-pennsylvania/ |title = LIHI Certificate #116 - Holtwood Project, Pennsylvania |author = The Low Impact Hydropower Institute |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-13 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210124223223/https://lowimpacthydro.org/lihi-certificate-116-holtwood-hydroelectric-project-pennsylvania/ |archivedate = 2021-01-24}}</ref>。特別的是，霍爾特伍德水壩頂部由木製閘板和[[充氣橡皮壩|充氣橡皮壩]]抬高，且未有裝設防洪閘<ref name="MD-DNR@2016_Appendix K"/><ref name="LIHI-Holtwood Dam"/>{{sfn|Langland|2009|p=11}}。此外，位於馬利蘭州、距離河口16公里（9.9英里）的{{tsl|en|Conowingo Dam|科諾溫哥水壩}}則在1928年啟用，它同屬混凝土重力壩，長1,417米（4,648英尺），高29米（94英尺）<ref name="Poindexter@HR_160708">{{Cite web |url = https://www.hydroreview.com/business-finance/maryland-forms-commission-to-study-sediment-issues-at-572-mw-conowingo-hydroelectric-facility/ |title = Maryland forms commission to study sediment issues at 572-MW Conowingo hydroelectric facility |last = Poindexter |first = Gregory |date = 2016-07-08 |publisher = Hydro Review |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-12 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210126193137/https://www.hydroreview.com/business-finance/maryland-forms-commission-to-study-sediment-issues-at-572-mw-conowingo-hydroelectric-facility/ |archivedate = 2021-01-26}}</ref>。科諾溫哥水庫的面積為36平方公里（9,000英畝），最大蓄水量為380,000,000立方米（310,000英畝·英尺）<ref name="Poindexter@HR_160708"/>。水壩設有2個調節閘門和50個防洪閘，可經由S形溢洪道把洪水排放至河內<ref name="MD-DNR@2016_Appendix K"/>。

除了水壩外，多個沿河而建的城市亦修築防洪堤系統來抵禦洪水。1935年，美國國會向美國陸軍工兵部隊撥款365萬美元，用以在賓夕法尼亞州懷俄明谷的河流沿岸修建防洪堤<ref name="LCFPA History">{{Cite web |url = http://www.lcfpa.org/history.html |title = LCFPA History |author = Luzerne County Flood Protection Authority |year = 2017 |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-13 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210426192227/http://www.lcfpa.org/history.html |archivedate = 2021-04-26}}</ref>。防洪堤的預定高度為10米（33英尺），稍高於當時河流的最高水位8.7米（28.6英尺）<ref name="LCFPA History"/>。然而，1936年的洪水導致河流水位略高於防洪堤，並在該區造成廣泛破壞<ref name="LCFPA History"/>。洪水過後，區內各個市政府加緊修建防洪設施，終以79.3萬美元建造了長約2,000米（6,400英尺）的防洪堤<ref name="LCFPA History"/>。同年6月22日《{{tsl|en|Flood Control Act of 1936|1936年防洪法|防洪法}}》通過，授權工兵部隊在紐約州和賓州建造蓄水池和相關防洪項目，以保護城市及其周邊地區免受頻發洪水影響及降低損失<ref name="LCFPA History"/><ref name="Binghamton Flood Control@NYSDEC">{{Cite web |url = https://www.dec.ny.gov/docs/water_pdf/fcpprjbinghm.pdf |title = BINGHAMTON FLOOD DAMAGE REDUCTION PROJECT |author = New York State Department of Environmental Conservation |publisher = State of New York |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-14 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20191103033808/https://www.dec.ny.gov/docs/water_pdf/fcpprjbinghm.pdf |archivedate = 2019-11-03}}</ref>。自1940年起，工兵部隊在紐約州賓漢頓地區先後興建多項防洪設施，包括長28.2公里（17.5英里）的土堤、長4.8公里（3英里）的混凝土防洪牆、179個分段閘門、一個水庫和20個防洪湖泊<ref name="Binghamton Flood Control@NYSDEC"/><ref name="Crable@BJ_201207">{{Cite web |url = https://www.bayjournal.com/news/climate_change/floods-drive-binghamton-toward-sea-change-of-resiliency/article_e75c7f86-354d-11eb-b83f-ab0b9281bf63.html |title = Floods drive Binghamton toward sea change of resiliency |last = Crable |first = Ad |date = 2020-12-07 |publisher = Bay Journal |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-14 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210118201656/https://www.bayjournal.com/news/climate_change/floods-drive-binghamton-toward-sea-change-of-resiliency/article_e75c7f86-354d-11eb-b83f-ab0b9281bf63.html |archivedate = 2021-01-18}}</ref>。此外，工兵部隊亦清理鄰近賓漢頓的河道和河岸，以及利用{{tsl|en|Riprap|拋石工法}}以保護河岸<ref name="Binghamton Flood Control@NYSDEC"/><ref name="Crable@BJ_201207"/>。1975年颶風艾格尼絲和[[颶風埃洛伊塞|颶風埃洛伊塞]]過後，賓漢頓一帶得益於工兵部隊所建的防洪設施而並未受嚴重影響<ref name="Crable@BJ_201207"/>，而賓州路澤恩縣則受災嚴重，故縣政府耗資2億美元提升區內防洪設施，包括把長約26公里（16英里）的防洪堤增高0.91至1.5米（3至5英尺），改良13個聯邦抽水站的結構，以及改善排水和封閉結構<ref name="LCFPA History"/>。在2011年熱帶風暴李所誘發的洪災過後，路澤恩縣政府再次強化當地的防洪牆<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.nab.usace.army.mil/Media/Images/igphoto/2000755212/ |title = Strengthening the Wyoming Valley floodwall |author = U.S. Army Corps of Engineers - Baltimore District |date = 2011-12-12 |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-14 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210614111633/https://www.nab.usace.army.mil/Media/Images/igphoto/2000755212/ |archivedate = 2021-06-14}}</ref>，而賓漢頓市政府則釋出面積約0.59平方公里（146英畝）的氾濫平原土地改為城市綠地用途以作緩衝，又在基建設施附近加建防洪牆<ref name="Crable@BJ_201207"/>。另外，哈里斯堡只在沿河的哈里斯堡國際機場外修建防洪堤，以防止洪水淹沒機場跑道，卻未有在市內沿河地區修建相關建築<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://urbanengineers.com/projects/harrisburg-airport-flood-and-levee-system |title = Harrisburg International Airport - Flood Dike and Levee System Rehabilitation Project |author = Urban Engineers |language = en |accessdate = 2021-01-02 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210118191825/https://urbanengineers.com/projects/harrisburg-airport-flood-and-levee-system |archivedate = 2021-01-18}}</ref>{{sfn|Roland, et al.|2013|p=3}}。

== 環境影響 ==
[[File:Sediment_Clouds_the_Chesapeake_Bay_after_Tropical_Storm_Lee_(2011).jpg|thumb]]
薩斯奎哈納河流域委員會採用水質指數來評估基流條件下河溪的一般健康狀況<ref name="SRBC WQI Report 2020">{{Cite web |url = https://www.srbc.net/our-work/reports-library/technical-reports/322-water-quality-index-2020/docs/water-quality-index-2019.PDF |title = DEVELOPMENT OF A WATER QUALITY INDEX (WQI) FOR THE SUSQUEHANNA RIVER BASIN |last1 = Berry |first1 = Joanna L. |last2 = Steffy |first2 = Luanne Y. |last3 = Shank |first3 = Matthew K. |year = 2020 |publisher = Susquehanna River Basin Commission |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-19 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210410021846/https://www.srbc.net/our-work/reports-library/technical-reports/322-water-quality-index-2020/docs/water-quality-index-2019.PDF |archivedate = 2021-04-10}}</ref>。按照污染程度，指數把河溪水質大致分為五個級別：極佳、良好、普通、惡劣、極劣<ref name="SRBC WQI Report 2020"/>。根據薩斯奎哈納河流域委員會在2020年發表的報告，河流水質介乎良好與普通之間，但同時部分監測站所得的水質數據屬惡劣，另有少部份地區的水質屬極佳或極劣<ref name="SRBC WQI Report 2020"/>。河流的主要污染物來源包括含有氮和磷元素的地表逕流（主要來自區內農場和已發展地區），長期積聚在水壩的沉積物，廢棄礦井的排水，以及老舊廢水處理設施的排放或洩漏等<ref name="CBF2006_Pollution">{{Cite web |url = https://www.nrc.gov/docs/ML0828/ML082880724.pdf |title = Waters At Risk: Pollution in the Susquehanna Watershed - Sources and Solutions |author = Chesapeake Bay Foundation |year = 2006 |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-19 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200416082258/https://www.nrc.gov/docs/ML0828/ML082880724.pdf |archivedate = 2020-04-16}}</ref><ref name="Argento@DA_210203">{{Cite web |url = https://www.dailyamerican.com/story/news/local/2021/02/03/pas-polluted-susquehanna-river-is-poisoning-the-bay-what-can-be-done/43601575/ |title = PA's polluted Susquehanna River is poisoning the bay. What can be done |last = Argento |first = Mike |date = 2021-02-03 |publisher = Daily American |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-20 |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20211109085231/https://www.dailyamerican.com/story/news/local/2021/02/03/pas-polluted-susquehanna-river-is-poisoning-the-bay-what-can-be-done/43601575/ |archivedate = 2021-11-09 }}</ref>。這些污染物除了危害河流健康外，亦會威脅其他河流使用者和野生動物的安全，並可能對經濟造成破壞性影響<ref name="Argento@DA_210203"/>。2016年，賓夕凡尼亞州環境保護部發表河流水質監測報告，指哈里斯堡河段的大腸菌群含量較高，並把鄰近8公里（5英里）的河段列為「受損」<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.pennlive.com/news/2016/08/impaired_waterways_not_necessa.html |title = Impaired waterways not necessarily unsafe for swimming, DEP says |last = Hardison |first = Lizzy |date = 2016-08-03 |publisher = PennLive.com |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-20 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200809170130/https://www.pennlive.com/news/2016/08/impaired_waterways_not_necessa.html |archivedate = 2020-08-09}}</ref>。2018年，紐約州賓漢頓政府把1.3億公升（3500萬美制加侖）未經處理的廢水排入河流<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.timesleader.com/news/715386/ny-plant-released-35m-gallons-of-untreated-waste-into-susquehanna |title = NY plant released 35M gallons of untreated waste into Susquehanna |last = Lewis |first = Ed |date = 2018-08-17 |publisher = Times Leader |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-20 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20190127023214/https://www.timesleader.com/news/715386/ny-plant-released-35m-gallons-of-untreated-waste-into-susquehanna |archivedate = 2019-01-27}}</ref>。而在2020年，環保組織「下薩斯奎哈納河守護者」發表同類報告，指哈里斯堡河段的大腸桿菌水平較游泳或水上娛樂的安全標準高出2.5倍以上，城市島沙灘公園亦因河水細菌含量高而被迫關閉，並把矛頭指向該市在風暴期間把雨水和受污染廢水混合排放至河流的做法<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://waterkeeperschesapeake.org/harrisburg-water-monitoring-shows-unsafe-levels-of-bacteria-in-33-of-tests-in-susquehanna-river-this-summer/ |title = Harrisburg Water Monitoring Shows Unsafe Levels of Bacteria in 33% of Tests in Susquehanna River this Summer |author = Waterkeepers Chesapeake |date = 2020-08-17 |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-20 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201204020803/https://waterkeeperschesapeake.org/harrisburg-water-monitoring-shows-unsafe-levels-of-bacteria-in-33-of-tests-in-susquehanna-river-this-summer/ |archivedate = 2020-12-04}}</ref>。另外，河流流域存在不少荒廢煤礦，這些橙黃色的煤礦排水通常含有高濃度的酸和有毒金屬，並會以滲入水道和小溪的形式破壞周遭環境和水中生態<ref name="CBF2006_Pollution"/>。

城市化也改變了河流中的沉積物輸送。沉積物和有毒物質會隨著城市逕流進入河流，污染和干擾水中生態<ref name="CBF2006_Pollution"/>。部分化學物質例如磷和氮更會造成[[優養化|優養化]]，甚至產生大面積的死區​<ref name="CBF2006_Pollution"/>。另外，河流下游數座大型水壩捕獲和儲存大量沉積物，從根本上改變了蓄水區的棲息地生態<ref name="CBF2006_Pollution"/>。雖然這些水壩暫時阻止沉積物移動並污染下游，但它們將會在未來達到容量上限後開始向海灣輸送{{sfn|Langland|2015|p=17}}。另一邊廂，水壩在強風暴侵襲時會打開防洪閘泄洪，使大量沉積物和污染物順流而下<ref name="Rentsch@DelmarvaNow_210203">{{Cite web |url = https://www.delmarvanow.com/in-depth/news/2021/02/02/conowingo-dams-toxic-muck-vexing-problem-chesapeake-bay-susquehanna-river/3258294001/ |title = Dammed if you dredge, dammed if you don't: Conowingo's toxic muck a vexing problem for bay |last = Rentsch |first = Julia |date = 2021-02-03 |publisher = DelmarvaNow.com |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-21 |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20211109081219/https://www.delmarvanow.com/in-depth/news/2021/02/02/conowingo-dams-toxic-muck-vexing-problem-chesapeake-bay-susquehanna-river/3258294001/ |archivedate = 2021-11-09 }}</ref>。2011年熱帶風暴李吹襲期間，下游水壩一度向車薩比灣排放輸送沉積物<ref name="Rentsch@DelmarvaNow_210203"/>。2015年，美國地質調查局確認1972年颶風艾格尼絲為科諾溫哥水壩帶來1350萬噸沉積物<ref name="Rentsch@DelmarvaNow_210203"/>。據估計，現時每年約有230萬噸沉積物經由河流輸送至海灣，另約有340萬噸則被困於河流下游的三座主要水壩{{sfn|Langland|2015|p=17}}。水壩的建設亦會影響常棲魚和洄游魚族群的數量<ref name="CBF2006_Pollution"/>。河流流域曾是美國東海岸最大的美洲西鯡產卵區，歷史上有數以百萬計的美洲西鯡洄游至河流產卵<ref name="CBF2006_Pollution"/>。然而，基於水壩的阻擋，現時只有約2%的美洲西鯡能抵達河流上游的產卵棲地<ref name="CBF2006_Pollution"/>。

== 保育與修復 ==
在確定水質狀況方面，薩斯奎哈納河流域委員會會透過數種方法來收集相關數據，包括從河溪中取出水樣，歸納和評估河流生物群落的健康狀況，評估河岸條件、沉積程度和理想棲息地的可得性，以及研究如流量和降水等環境條件<ref name="SRBC2017_Water Quality Monitoring">{{Cite web |url = https://www.srbc.net/our-work/fact-sheets/docs/water-quality-monitoring.pdf |title = Water Quality Monitoring in The Susquehanna River Basin |author = Susquehanna River Basin Commission |year = 2017 |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-23 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210318031150/https://www.srbc.net/our-work/fact-sheets/docs/water-quality-monitoring.pdf |archivedate = 2021-03-18}}</ref>。雖然委員會不直接監管水質，但他們仍會與機構和其他利益相關者分享數據和協調，以確保決策者採取行動防止或解決水質問題<ref name="SRBC2017_Water Quality Monitoring"/>。在改善水質方面，除了硬件改善（如升級污水處理廠設備和在河岸安裝侵蝕控制裝置）外，三州政府都推行了不同措施減輕河流污染程度<ref name="CBF2006_Pollution"/>。以紐約州為例，政府推出了不同計劃協助當區農民轉型至有機農業，及改善牲畜排泄物收集方式，以減少化肥、農藥和動物糞便流入河流的機會<ref name="CBF2006_Pollution"/><ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.nrcs.usda.gov/wps/portal/nrcs/detail/ny/technical/?cid=nrcs144p2_027110 |title = New York and the Chesapeake Bay Watershed |author = NRCS New York |publisher = U.S. Department of Agriculture |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-24 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210323080556/https://www.nrcs.usda.gov/wps/portal/nrcs/detail/ny/technical/?cid=nrcs144p2_027110 |archivedate = 2021-03-23}}</ref>。為防廢棄礦井的排水繼續污染河溪，賓夕凡尼亞州政府建造了各種被動修復系統以降低水的酸度和去除有毒金屬，其中包括在明渠鋪上石灰石降低流水的酸度和提高其pH值，以及積蓄污水並待氧化鐵沉澱後再排放到鄰近溪流<ref name="CBF2006_Pollution"/><ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.pennlive.com/news/2018/07/anthracite_minings_long_legacy.html |title = Why some Pa. streams and rivers are orange: the legacy of abandoned mines |last = Malawskey |first = Nick |date = 2018-07-31 |publisher = PennLive.com |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-26 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201125030753/https://www.pennlive.com/news/2018/07/anthracite_minings_long_legacy.html |archivedate = 2020-11-25}}</ref>。針對水壩沉積物，馬利蘭州政府祭出數項解決方法，包括定時疏浚沉積物並利用綠化技術把其循環再用，製定水體可以接受的最大污染物量「{{tsl|en|Total maximum daily load|總最大日負荷}}」等<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.delmarvanow.com/story/news/2020/11/19/maryland-begin-sediment-project-behind-conowingo-dam/6328910002/ |title = Maryland to begin sediment dredging and reuse project behind Conowingo Dam |last = Rentsch |first = Julia |date = 2020-11-19 |publisher = DelmarvaNow.com |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-26 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210226045140/https://www.delmarvanow.com/story/news/2020/11/19/maryland-begin-sediment-project-behind-conowingo-dam/6328910002/ |archivedate = 2021-02-26}}</ref>。另外，馬利蘭州政府亦在2019年與科諾溫哥水壩的營運商艾索倫電力公司達成協議，以新的50年水壩營運許可證換取公司撥款約2億美元改善包括水質等問題<ref name="Rentsch@DN_191029">{{Cite web |url = https://www.delmarvanow.com/story/news/2019/10/29/conowingo-dam-legal-battle-ends-200-m-settlement-bay-restoration/2496079001/ |title = Conowingo Dam legal battle ends with $200M settlement for bay restoration |last = Rentsch |first = Julia |date = 2019-10-29 |publisher = DelmarvaNow.com |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-26 |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20211109081316/https://www.delmarvanow.com/story/news/2019/10/29/conowingo-dam-legal-battle-ends-200-m-settlement-bay-restoration/2496079001/ |archivedate = 2021-11-09 }}</ref>。

雖然天然植被覆蓋率高達六成，但流域內仍有36%的河溪未被森林緩衝帶覆蓋，而在下游地區比例更上升至50%<ref name="Forest-Buffer-Toolkit">{{Cite web |url = https://www.dep.state.pa.us/dep/deputate/watermgt/wc/Subjects/StreamReleaf/Forestbufftool/tkit_main.pdf |title = Pennsylvania Stream ReLeaf Forest Buffer Toolkit |author = Alliancefor the Chesapeake Bay |year = 1998 |publisher = Pennsylvania Department of Environmental Protection, Bureau of Watershed Conservation |language = en |accessdate = 2021-04-07 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20170429193254/http://www.dep.state.pa.us/dep/deputate/watermgt/wc/Subjects/StreamReleaf/Forestbufftool/tkit_main.pdf |archivedate = 2017-04-29}}</ref>。為了修復因人類活動而造成的[[棲息地破碎化|棲息地破碎化]]，多州傾向優先保護森林樞紐、走廊和濕地，以加強現時野生動物正在使用的剩餘生境網絡，以及提供額外的森林內部棲息地<ref name="Chesapeake Forest Restoration@2012">{{Cite web |url = https://federalleadership.chesapeakebay.net/chesapeakeforestrestorationstrategy.pdf |title = Chesapeake Forest Restoration Strategy |author = Chesapeake Bay Program |year = 2012 |publisher = U.S. Forest Service |language = en |accessdate = 2021-04-11 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200719225520/https://federalleadership.chesapeakebay.net/chesapeakeforestrestorationstrategy.pdf |archivedate = 2020-07-19}}</ref>。賓夕法尼亞州政府在美國國家環境保護局的支持下展開州內評估工作，而美國魚類及野生動物管理局亦與紐約州的環保組織上薩斯奎哈納自然保護聯盟合作，透過生態數據來確定保護和恢復區域的優先順序，旨在確保森林恢復工作能對魚類和野生動植物棲息地產生最大效益<ref name="Chesapeake Forest Restoration@2012"/>。此外，聯邦政府和各州的合作夥伴承諾，將會在2025年恢復車薩比灣流域68%的沿岸森林覆蓋率，並訂下每年恢復1,400公里（900英里）的目標<ref name="Chesapeake Forest Restoration@2012"/>。2017年，約50名義工在蘭開斯特縣的下游-{}-河溪兩岸種植逾800棵樹，以加強河岸穩定性和向魚類種群提供棲息地<ref name="Koch@170620">{{Cite web |url = https://extension.psu.edu/lower-susquehanna-community-saving-a-stream-using-trees |title = Lower Susquehanna Community Saving a Stream Using Trees |last = Koch |first = Kristen |date = 2017-06-20 |publisher = PennState Extension |language = en |accessdate = 2021-04-11 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201022064332/https://extension.psu.edu/lower-susquehanna-community-saving-a-stream-using-trees |archivedate = 2020-10-22}}</ref>。針對廢棄礦山問題，賓夕凡尼亞州政府在2009年曾批出多份合同以復墾礦山及其高牆，以及回填礦井<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/dep-restores-750-acres-of-dangerous-abandoned-mine-lands-begins-construction-on-two-major-mine-drainage-treatment-plants-86406132.html |title = DEP Restores 750 Acres of Dangerous Abandoned Mine Lands, Begins Construction on Two Major Mine Drainage Treatment Plants |author = Pennsylvania Department of Environmental Protection |date = 2010-03-04 |publisher = PR Newswire |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-27 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210627075821/https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/dep-restores-750-acres-of-dangerous-abandoned-mine-lands-begins-construction-on-two-major-mine-drainage-treatment-plants-86406132.html |archivedate = 2021-06-27}}</ref>。為修復土地和減低污染物流入河流的機會，非牟利組織{{tsl|en|Chesapeake Bay Foundation|車薩比灣基金會}}與賓夕法尼亞州政府、賓夕法尼亞州環境委員會和薩斯奎哈納河流域委員會合作，在廢棄礦地上種植樹木試圖重建森林<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.cbf.org/blogs/save-the-bay/2020/06/reclaiming-polluted-mine-land.html |title = Reclaiming Polluted Mine Land |last = Small |first = B.J. |date = 2020-06-30 |publisher = Chesapeake Bay Foundation |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-27 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200831215803/https://www.cbf.org/blogs/save-the-bay/2020/06/reclaiming-polluted-mine-land.html |archivedate = 2020-08-31}}</ref>。

1942年，時任總統[[富蘭克林·德拉諾·羅斯福|富蘭克林·德拉諾·羅斯福]]簽署9185號行政命令，把河口至車薩比灣頂部一帶劃為野生動物保護區，以保護候鳥和其他野生動植物{{sfn|The National Archives|1943|p=1171}}<ref name="SRNWR_About the Refuge">{{Cite web |url = https://www.fws.gov/refuge/Susquehanna/about.html |title = About the Refuge |author = U.S. Fish & Wildlife Service |publisher = Department of the Interior |language = en |accessdate = 2021-04-11 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210403000215/https://www.fws.gov/refuge/Susquehanna/about.html |archivedate = 2021-03-04}}</ref>。在高峰期間，{{tsl|en|Susquehanna River National Wildlife Refuge|薩斯奎哈納河國家野生動物保護區}}一度錄得逾50萬頭[[帆背潛鴨|帆背潛鴨]]和[[美洲潜鸭|美洲潜鸭]]，以及逾20萬頭[[葡萄胸鴨|葡萄胸鴨]]<ref name="SRNWR_About the Refuge"/>。另外，河流流域曾經是多種魚類的棲息地，但受到如水壩建設等人類活動的影響，魚類數目急速下降<ref name="NYDEC_Restoration Plan">{{Cite web |url = https://www.dec.ny.gov/outdoor/80254.html |title = Migratory Fish Management and Restoration Plan for the Susquehanna River Basin |author = New York State Department of Environmental Conservation |publisher = State of New York |language = en |accessdate = 2021-04-11 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20191102173917/http://www.dec.ny.gov/outdoor/80254.html |archivedate = 2019-11-02}}</ref><ref name="SRAFRC_Restoration Plan">{{Cite web |url = https://www.nrc.gov/docs/ML0823/ML082381108.pdf |title = Migratory Fish Management and Restoration Plan for the Susquehanna River Basin |author = The Susquehanna River Anadromous Fish Restoration Cooperative |publisher = U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service |language = en |accessdate = 2021-04-11 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20211109081414/https://www.nrc.gov/docs/ML0823/ML082381108.pdf |archivedate = 2021-11-09 }}</ref>。由三州漁業機構、薩斯奎哈納河流域委員會和聯邦政府組成的薩斯奎哈納河洄游魚類恢復合作社（{{lang|en|The Susquehanna River Anadromous Fish Restoration Cooperative}}）編寫了《魚類遷徙管理和恢復計劃》，用以修復流域的魚類棲息地和移除障礙物，以及確保魚類能洄游至流域上游產卵，最終達致提升魚類種群數量和恢復流域漁業可持續的目標<ref name="NYDEC_Restoration Plan"/><ref name="SRAFRC_Restoration Plan"/>。針對淡水貽貝，除了1973年生效的《{{tsl|en|Endangered Species Act of 1973|1973年瀕臨滅絕物種法|瀕臨滅絕物種法}}》，紐約州政府還訂立了相關法規來防止公眾拾取和收穫瀕危物種，而賓夕法尼亞州政府更把法例覆蓋至屬於入侵物種的貽貝<ref name="USFWS_Pearly Mussels">{{Cite web |url = https://www.fws.gov/northeast/nyfo/usca/files/Pearly%20Mussels%20of%20the%20Susquehanna%20Basin%20FINAL.pdf |title = Pearly Mussels of the Susquehanna Basin |author = U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service |language = en |accessdate = 2021-04-11 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210411085238/https://www.fws.gov/northeast/nyfo/usca/files/Pearly%20Mussels%20of%20the%20Susquehanna%20Basin%20FINAL.pdf |archivedate = 2021-04-11}}</ref><ref name="PFBC@180209">{{Cite web |url = https://pa.fisheries.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Mussel-ID-workshop-field-guide-2-9-18.pdf |title = A Field Guide to Pennsylvania’s Freshwater Mussels |author = Pennsylvania Fish & Boat Commission |date = 2018-02-09 |language = en |accessdate = 2021-04-11 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201009122952/https://pa.fisheries.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Mussel-ID-workshop-field-guide-2-9-18.pdf |archivedate = 2020-10-09}}</ref>。2019年，賓夕法尼亞州基礎設施投資局與非牟利組織{{tsl|en|Partnership for the Delaware Estuary|德拉瓦河河口夥伴關係}}簽署資助協議，計劃在[[費城|費城]]西南部的{{tsl|en|Bartram's Garden|巴特拉姆花園}}附近興建淡水貽貝孵化場，培養對水質改善功效最大的常見貽貝物種，並定期把它們放入[[德拉瓦河|德拉瓦河]]和薩斯奎哈納河<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.hatcheryinternational.com/us79m-funding-for-freshwater-mussel-hatchery-in-pennsylvania-3528/ |title = US$7.9M funding for freshwater mussel hatchery in Pennsylvania |last = Waycott |first = Bonnie |date = 2019-06-25 |publisher = Hatchery International |language = en |accessdate = 2021-04-11 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210121233545/https://www.hatcheryinternational.com/us79m-funding-for-freshwater-mussel-hatchery-in-pennsylvania-3528/ |archivedate = 2021-01-21}}</ref>。同年，馬利蘭州政府與艾索倫電力公司達成協議，後者會投資數千萬美元改善下游生態系統，為洄游魚類提供更好的通道前往上游，並在流域建造貽貝孵化場<ref name="Rentsch@DN_191029"/>。而在解決入侵物種問題方面，{{tsl|en|Pennsylvania Department of Conservation and Natural Resources|賓夕法尼亞州自然資源保護部}}在2009年參與由跨機構組織賓夕法尼亞州入侵物種委員會（{{lang|en|Pennsylvania Invasive Species Council}}）牽頭的入侵物種管理計劃，並共同制定應對框架<ref name="DCNR_Invasive Plants">{{Cite web |url = https://www.dcnr.pa.gov/Conservation/WildPlants/InvasivePlants/pages/default.aspx |title = Invasive Plants in Pennsylvania |author = Pennsylvania Department of Conservation and Natural Resources |language = en |accessdate = 2021-04-07 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210319082837/https://www.dcnr.pa.gov/Conservation/WildPlants/InvasivePlants/Pages/default.aspx |archivedate = 2021-03-19}}</ref>。部門亦加強推廣有關入侵植物的知識，並向林業人員、公園工作人員以及公眾提供相關物種識別和控制的培訓<ref name="DCNR_Invasive Plants"/>。此外，賓夕法尼亞州農業部和有害雜草委員會在2020年初亦考慮把虎杖等六種入侵植物列入有害雜草清單，以阻止這些物種被引進和傳播至州內<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.pennlive.com/life/2020/01/more-killer-weeds-under-consideration-for-pennsylvanias-noxious-list.html |title = More killer weeds under consideration for Pennsylvania’s noxious list |last = Schneck |first = Marcus |date = 2020-01-21 |publisher = PennLive.com |language = en |accessdate = 2021-04-07 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201102204129/https://www.pennlive.com/life/2020/01/more-killer-weeds-under-consideration-for-pennsylvanias-noxious-list.html |archivedate = 2020-11-02}}</ref>。至於針對斑馬貽貝和黑口新鰕虎魚這些入侵動物，由於牠們較難去除，漁業管理人員只能透過化學物質來限制入侵，而政府亦已訂立法規來減緩或防止它們擴散{{sfn|Ashton|Klauda|2015|p=195}}{{sfn|Schreier|Dawson|Larson|2008|p=253}}。

== 休閒 ==
[[File:Rglenn05.jpg|thumb]]
薩斯奎哈納河流域共有75個州立公園和155個州立森林，其中賓夕凡尼亞州的州立公園和州立森林面積都較其他兩州廣闊<ref name="SRBC_Recreation">{{Cite web |url = https://www.srbc.net/portals/susquehanna-atlas/data-and-maps/recreation/ |title = Recreation |author = Susquehanna River Basin Commission |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-30 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210320202317/https://www.srbc.net/portals/susquehanna-atlas/data-and-maps/recreation/ |archivedate = 2021-03-20}}</ref>。紐約州的{{tsl|en|Robert V. Riddell State Park|羅伯特·V·里德爾州立公園}}，賓夕凡尼亞州的{{tsl|en|Ricketts Glen State Park|里基茨峽谷州立公園}}、{{tsl|en|Black Moshannon State Park|黑莫香農州立公園}}和{{tsl|en|Blue Knob State Park|布盧山州立公園}}，以及馬里蘭州的[[薩斯奎哈納州立公園_(馬里蘭州)|薩斯奎哈納州立公園]]是區內面積較大的公園<ref name="SRBC_Recreation"/>。區內佔地較廣的州立森林大多位於西部支流，其中包括{{tsl|en|Moshannon State Forest|莫香農州立森林}}、{{tsl|en|Sproul State Forest|斯普魯爾州立森林}}、{{tsl|en|Elk State Forest|艾烏克州立森林}}、{{tsl|en|Susquehannock State Forest|薩斯奎漢諾克州立森林}}和{{tsl|en|Quehanna Wild Area|奎哈納野生保護區}}等<ref name="SRBC_Recreation"/>{{sfn|Michaels|2003|pp=68, 75, 80, 100}}。這些公園和森林通常設有露營區、小木屋和野餐亭等設施，公眾可在此露營、野餐、划艇、釣魚和狩獵{{sfn|Michaels|2003|pp=68, 75, 80, 100}}<ref name="Robert V. Riddell State Park">{{Cite web |url = https://parks.ny.gov/parks/18/details.aspx |title = Robert V. Riddell State Park |author = New York State Parks Recreation & Historic Preservation |publisher = New York State |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-30 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210506135604/https://parks.ny.gov/parks/18/details.aspx |archivedate = 2021-05-06}}</ref><ref name="Ricketts Glen State Park">{{Cite web |url = https://www.dcnr.pa.gov/StateParks/FindAPark/RickettsGlenStatePark/Pages/default.aspx |title = Ricketts Glen State Park |author = Pennsylvania Department of Conservation and Natural Resources |publisher = Commonwealth of Pennsylvania |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-30 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210611010922/https://www.dcnr.pa.gov/StateParks/FindAPark/RickettsGlenStatePark/Pages/default.aspx |archivedate = 2021-06-11}}</ref><ref name="Blue Knob State Park">{{Cite web |url = https://www.dcnr.pa.gov/StateParks/FindAPark/BlueKnobStatePark/Pages/default.aspx |title = Blue Knob State Park |author = Pennsylvania Department of Conservation and Natural Resources |publisher = Commonwealth of Pennsylvania |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-30 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210507102202/https://www.dcnr.pa.gov/StateParks/FindAPark/BlueKnobStatePark/Pages/default.aspx |archivedate = 2021-05-07}}</ref><ref name="Susquehanna State Park">{{Cite web |url = https://dnr.maryland.gov/publiclands/Pages/central/susquehanna.aspx |title = Susquehanna State Park |author = Maryland Department of Natural Resources |publisher = State of Maryland |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-30 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210513072609/https://dnr.maryland.gov/publiclands/Pages/central/susquehanna.aspx |archivedate = 2021-05-13}}</ref>。另外，部份公園和森林還設有長達數十公里且難度不一的遠足徑，公眾甚至可在徑上騎馬、騎乘登山車和越野滑雪{{sfn|Michaels|2003|pp=68, 75, 80, 100}}<ref name="Robert V. Riddell State Park"/><ref name="Ricketts Glen State Park"/><ref name="Blue Knob State Park"/><ref name="Susquehanna State Park"/>。每逢3月至11月，里基茨峽谷州立公園更提供導賞服務，公眾可藉此了解園內的自然濕地、原始森林、瀑布、動植物群和地質構造<ref name="Ricketts Glen State Park"/>。

2019年，美國國會基於賓夕法尼亞州蘭開斯特縣和約克縣有著相近的歷史和風景優美的景觀，而把兩縣劃為{{tsl|en|Susquehanna National Heritage Area|薩斯奎哈納河國家遺產區}}<ref name="NPS_SNHA">{{Cite web |url = https://www.nps.gov/places/susquehanna-national-heritage-area.htm |title = Susquehanna National Heritage Area |author = National Park Service |publisher = U.S. Department of the Interior |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-27 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210309174338/https://www.nps.gov/places/susquehanna-national-heritage-area.htm |archivedate = 2021-03-09}}</ref>。區內設有兩個河畔遊客中心，分別是位於約克縣賴茨維爾以南的齊默爾曼遺產中心，以及位於蘭開斯特縣哥倫比亞的哥倫比亞跨河步道中心<ref name="NPS_SNHA"/>。兩個遊客中心均設有各式展覽，公眾可從中了解地區歷史和文化等資訊<ref name="NPS_SNHA"/>。此外，公眾可在特定季節前往齊默爾曼遺產中心乘船遊覽河流，以及經哥倫比亞跨河步道中心前往長23公里（14英里）且沿河鋪設的蘭開斯特縣西北河流步道（{{lang|en|Northwest Lancaster County River Trail}}）<ref name="NPS_SNHA"/>。薩斯奎哈納河水道（{{lang|en|Susquehanna River Water Trail}}）全長85公里（53英里），始於哈里斯堡，終於[[梅森-迪克森線|梅森-迪克森線]]以南的馬利蘭州一處<ref name="SRWT">{{Cite web |url = https://susquehannariverlands.com/the-great-outdoors/on-the-water/water-trails/susquehanna-river-water-trail/ |title = Susquehanna River Water Trail |author = Susquehanna Riverlands |language = en |accessdate = 2021-07-01 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210123021837/https://susquehannariverlands.com/the-great-outdoors/on-the-water/water-trails/susquehanna-river-water-trail/ |archivedate = 2021-01-23}}</ref>。水道沿途設有30多個船艇下水點，而它同時亦是其中一條[[國家休閒步道|國家休閒步道]]<ref name="SRWT"/>。位於蘭開斯特縣的康奈斯托加河水道（{{lang|en|Conestoga River Water Trail}}）全長97公里（60英里），是-{划}-輕艇和皮艇的熱門地點，而它亦屬縣內其中一條風景優美河流<ref name="CRWT">{{Cite web |url = https://susquehannariverlands.com/the-great-outdoors/on-the-water/water-trails/conestoga-river-water-trail/ |title = Conestoga River Water Trail |author = Susquehanna Riverlands |language = en |accessdate = 2021-07-01 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210122185317/http://susquehannariverlands.com/the-great-outdoors/on-the-water/water-trails/conestoga-river-water-trail/ |archivedate = 2021-01-22}}</ref>。{{tsl|en|Captain John Smith Chesapeake National Historic Trail|約翰史密斯船長車薩比國家歷史步道}}是美國第一條以水為基礎的國家歷史步道，由當時史密夫船長的航行路線組合而成<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://susquehannariverlands.com/the-great-outdoors/on-the-water/water-trails/captain-john-smith-chesapeake-national-historic-trail/ |title = Captain John Smith Chesapeake National Historic Trail |author = Susquehanna Riverlands |language = en |accessdate = 2021-07-01 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210124062438/http://susquehannariverlands.com/the-great-outdoors/on-the-water/water-trails/captain-john-smith-chesapeake-national-historic-trail/ |archivedate = 2021-01-24}}</ref>。2012年，內政部把整條河流指定為該步道的一部分<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.nps.gov/cajo/getinvolved/management-plan-for-the-trail.htm |title = Establishment & Management of the Trail |author = National Park Service |publisher = U.S. Department of the Interior |language = en |accessdate = 2021-07-01 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210407213546/https://www.nps.gov/cajo/getinvolved/management-plan-for-the-trail.htm |archivedate = 2021-04-07}}</ref>。公眾可在此-{划}-船、進行[[地理藏寶|地理藏寶]]和收集各種護照印章等活動<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.nps.gov/cajo/planyourvisit/things2do.htm |title = Captain John Smith Chesapeake National Historic Trail - Things To Do |author = National Park Service |publisher = U.S. Department of the Interior |language = en |accessdate = 2021-06-27 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210404211800/https://www.nps.gov/cajo/planyourvisit/things2do.htm |archivedate = 2021-04-04}}</ref>。

賽艇在流域內有著悠久歷史，每年均有多項賽事在此舉行。在每年的[[亡兵紀念日|亡兵紀念日]]週末，克林頓將軍獨木舟會均會舉行為期4日的克林頓將軍獨木舟比賽（{{lang|en|General Clinton Canoe Regatta}}），賽道長約110公里（70英里），始於奧齊戈湖終於[[班布里奇_(紐約州)|班布里奇]]，另附設嘉年華遊樂設施和煙花表演等娛樂活動<ref name="GCCR">{{Cite web |url = https://www.canoeregatta.org/ |title = General Clinton Canoe Regatta |author = General Clinton Canoe Regatta |language = en |accessdate = 2021-07-02 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210531062459/https://www.canoeregatta.org/ |archivedate = 2021-05-31}}</ref>。賽事自1963年起延續至今，每年都有超過1,000名獨木舟選手參賽，並吸引逾萬名觀眾<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.evesun.com/news/stories/2009-05-22/7022/Bainbridge-Canoe-Regatta-this-weekend |title = Bainbridge Canoe Regatta This Weekend |last = Stagnaro |first = Melissa |date = 2009-05-22 |publisher = The EveningSun |language = en |accessdate = 2021-07-03 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150910150825/http://www.evesun.com/news/stories/2009-05-22/7022/Bainbridge-Canoe-Regatta-this-weekend/ |archivedate = 2015-09-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.newyorkupstate.com/outdoors/2016/05/general_clinton_canoe_regatta_the_one_everyone_wants_to_do.html |title = General Clinton Canoe Regatta on Memorial Day: 'The one everyone wants to do' |last = Figura |first = David |date = 2016-05-23 |publisher = NYup.com |language = en |accessdate = 2021-07-03 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160531015817/https://www.newyorkupstate.com/outdoors/2016/05/general_clinton_canoe_regatta_the_one_everyone_wants_to_do.html |archivedate = 2016-05-03}}</ref>。但在2020年[[2019冠狀病毒病美國疫情|新冠肺炎疫情]]的影響下，2020年未有舉辦，而2021年則改為虛擬比賽<ref name="GCCR"/>。另外，賓漢頓大學賽艇會自1998年以來，每年都會在賓漢頓以西的河段舉辦布斯菲爾德紀念賽船大會（{{lang|en|Busfield Memorial Regatta}}），賽事分為男子組和女子組，而參賽者則以三州大學賽艇會為主<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.regattacentral.com/regatta/?job_id=6301 |title = 21st Annual Busfield Memorial Regatta |author = Regatta Central |year = 2019 |language = en |accessdate = 2021-07-02 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20190411063714/https://www.regattacentral.com/regatta/?job_id=6301 |archivedate = 2019-04-11}}</ref>。但同樣因受2020年新冠肺炎疫情影響，2020年賽事宣告取消<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.regattacentral.com/regatta/index.jsp?job_id=6942&org_id=0 |title = 22nd Annual Busfield Regatta |author = Regatta Central |year = 2020 |language = en |accessdate = 2021-07-02 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210702144135/https://www.regattacentral.com/regatta/index.jsp?job_id=6942&org_id=0 |archivedate = 2021-07-02}}</ref>。除了賽艇比賽，河上亦不時有各種慶典活動舉行，例如在森伯里舉辦的森伯里河流節（{{lang|en|Sunbury River Festival}}）<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://sunburyrevitalization.org/events-programs/sunbury-river-festival/ |title = Sunbury River Festival |author = Sunbury’s Revitalization |language = en |accessdate = 2021-07-03 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210703155639/https://sunburyrevitalization.org/events-programs/sunbury-river-festival/ |archivedate = 2021-07-03}}</ref>，在劉易斯堡舉辦的薩斯奎哈納-{划}-艇電影節（{{lang|en|Susquehanna Float & Films}}）<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.dailyitem.com/applause/kayakers-to-voyage-to-campus-theatre-for-susquehanna-float-films-event/article_e077ea48-d3ea-11eb-9087-f3783c952b45.html |title = Susquehanna Float & Films wants you to canoe-in to an international film festival |last = Schad |first = Ben |date = 2021-06-21 |publisher = ABC27 News |language = en |accessdate = 2021-07-03 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210629001829/https://www.abc27.com/community/forget-a-drive-in-susquehanna-float-films-wants-you-to-canoe-in-to-an-international-film-festival/ |archivedate = 2021-06-29}}</ref>，以及在哈弗格雷斯舉行的薩斯奎哈納河跑步節（{{lang|en|Susquehanna River Running Festival}}）<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://runsignup.com/Race/MD/HavredeGrace/SRRF2019 |title = Susquehanna River Running Festival |author = RunSignup |language = en |accessdate = 2021-07-03 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210703155825/https://runsignup.com/Race/MD/HavredeGrace/SRRF2019 |archivedate = 2021-07-03}}</ref>等。

流域同時是觀鳥的絕佳地點，多個[[重點鳥區|重點鳥區]]均位於區內，包括卡茨基爾峰區（{{lang|en|Catskills Peaks Area}}）<ref name="Audubon_Catskills">{{Cite web |url = https://www.audubon.org/important-bird-areas/catskills-peaks-area |title = Important Bird Areas: Catskills Peaks Area, New York |author = National Audubon Society |language = en |accessdate = 2021-07-01 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210123181205/https://www.audubon.org/important-bird-areas/catskills-peaks-area |archivedate = 2021-01-23}}</ref>、薩斯奎哈納河源森林區塊（{{lang|en|Susquehanna Headwaters Forest Block}}）<ref name="Audubon_SHFB">{{Cite web |url = https://www.audubon.org/important-bird-areas/susquehanna-headwaters-forest-block |title = Important Bird Areas: Susquehanna Headwaters Forest Block, Pennsylvania |author = National Audubon Society |language = en |accessdate = 2021-07-01 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210227221006/https://www.audubon.org/important-bird-areas/susquehanna-headwaters-forest-block |archivedate = 2021-02-27}}</ref>、基塔廷尼嶺（{{lang|en|Kittatinny Ridge}}）<ref name="Audubon_Kittatinny">{{Cite web |url = https://www.audubon.org/important-bird-areas/kittatinny-ridge |title = Important Bird Areas: Kittatinny Ridge, Pennsylvania |author = National Audubon Society |language = en |accessdate = 2021-07-01 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201201201548/https://www.audubon.org/important-bird-areas/kittatinny-ridge |archivedate = 2020-12-01}}</ref>、{{tsl|en|Conejohela Flats|康尼尤赫拉淺灘}}<ref name="Audubon_Conejohela Flats"/>以及下薩斯奎哈納河峽谷（{{lang|en|Lower Susquehanna River Gorge}}）<ref name="Audubon_Conowingo/Muddy Run"/>等。除了不同種類的林鳥外<ref name="Audubon_Catskills"/><ref name="Audubon_SHFB"/><ref name="Audubon_Kittatinny"/>，公眾亦可在鄰近河口的鳥區內觀賞大藍鷺、小天鵝、斑腹磯鷸、{{tsl|en|American coot|美洲瓣蹼鷸}}、白頭海鵰等鳥類<ref name="Audubon_Conejohela Flats"/><ref name="Audubon_Conowingo/Muddy Run"/>。近年，下薩斯奎哈納河峽谷鳥區更成為白頭海鵰的聚集地，高峰時一度約有350隻聚集於此，吸引不少野生動物攝影師、觀鳥者和遊客前往區內的科諾溫哥水壩觀賞<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.bayjournal.com/travel/bald-eagle-ballet-thrills-tourists-photographers-at-conowingo-dam/article_082e280c-5913-11eb-b9cb-bbc2dce9ff79.html |title = Bald eagle ballet thrills tourists, photographers at Conowingo Dam |last = Crable |first = Ad |date = 2021-01-18 |publisher = Bay Journal |language = en |accessdate = 2021-07-01 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210323173129/https://www.bayjournal.com/travel/bald-eagle-ballet-thrills-tourists-photographers-at-conowingo-dam/article_082e280c-5913-11eb-b9cb-bbc2dce9ff79.html |archivedate = 2021-03-23}}</ref>。

